name: Warung Coffee Bali
address: HG6P+M4F, Sibetan, Bebandem, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80861, Indonesia
review 1: I was driving to Ubud and was getting sleepy. Found this establishment along the road and decided to stop by for some coffee. Didn't regret it a single bit. The cool wind was just perfect as I absorbed the serene view of terraced paddy fields below.
review 2: Perfect place for a stopover. A great place to catch your breath with a view of the rice terraces.  The warung has some local dishes but also foreign dishes like burgers.  We had two juices, one was pineapple/orange and the other was a mix of different fruits and both were very tasty.  The food was also very good and freshly made.  The chilli was freshly picked behind the house.  The owner and his family are very friendly.  Although it is right on the road, the small waterfall is louder than most cars and therefore perfectly ok.
review 3: Cute spot for a coffee, lunch and views.
review 4: Very nice place, good food, friendly owner, good prices and amazing view!
review 5: Friendly and welcoming staff, great view of rice fields and super tasty omelette with vegetables! What else?
